dition 33 walks through an underwater area.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"The cast of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 walks through an underwater area.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/335d899c377996583d8eb756ffcd381b.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/335d899c377996583d8eb756ffcd381b.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/335d899c377996583d8eb756ffcd381b.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"The cast of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 walks through an underwater area.\" data-chomp-id=\"335d899c377996583d8eb756ffcd381b\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"The cast of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 walks through an underwater area.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/335d899c377996583d8eb756ffcd381b.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Sandfall Interactive\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"335d899c377996583d8eb756ffcd381b\" data-recommend-id=\"image://335d899c377996583d8eb756ffcd381b\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The cast of Clair Obscur: Expedition 33 walks through an underwater area.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eClair Obscur: Expedition 33\u003c/em\u003e has all the makings of a modern turn-based classic. After playing a few hours of Sandfall Interactive’s dark fantasy RPG, I can say that \u003cem\u003eExpedition 33 \u003c/em\u003egrasps the melodrama of modern \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy\u003c/em\u003e and marries it with the tactical turn-based combat fans of that series have been craving a return to for decades. On top of this, the game also has a \u003cem\u003ePaper Mario\u003c/em\u003e-like timing mechanic to make that combat about more than just picking which attacks and items you use during a turn. Sandfall Interactive is cooking with some excellent ingredients, and the small taste I’ve gotten has me eager to try the full meal. - Kenneth Shepard \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-rpg-preview-turn-based-1851767119\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/clair-obscur-expedition-33-rpg-preview-turn-based-1851767119\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d\" data-recommend-id=\"image://61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1219\" data-height=\"685\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Suikoden 1 and 2 protagonists stand at attention. \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Suikoden 1 and 2 protagonists stand at attention. \" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Suikoden 1 and 2 protagonists stand at attention. \" data-chomp-id=\"61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"685\" data-alt=\"Suikoden 1 and 2 protagonists stand at attention. \" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Konami\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d\" data-recommend-id=\"image://61efc76c19ac41e8c7ec2de22c65183d\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1219\" data-height=\"685\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Suikoden 1 and 2 protagonists stand at attention. \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eAlmost every major Japanese publisher had to have a big RPG franchise in the PS1 era. Square Soft had \u003cem\u003eFinal Fantasy\u003c/em\u003e. Enix had \u003cem\u003eDragon Quest\u003c/em\u003e. Capcom had \u003cem\u003eBreath of Fire\u003c/em\u003e. Bandai Namco had \u003cem\u003eTales\u003c/em\u003e. \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/why-you-should-play-suikoden-ii-one-of-the-best-rpgs-e-1668857424?_gl=1*m34oo9*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTE5ODM3OC4zMC4wLjE3NDExOTgzNzguNjAuMC4w\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/why-you-should-play-suikoden-ii-one-of-the-best-rpgs-e-1668857424?_gl=1*m34oo9*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MTE5ODM3OC4zMC4wLjE3NDExOTgzNzguNjAuMC4w\"\u003eAnd so, Konami made \u003cem\u003eSuikoden\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e. Its innovation was trading a set party of heroes for a cast of 108 total characters who could be recruited on your adventure. Combined with a world of rune-based magic and political intrigue, \u003cem\u003eSuikoden I \u003c/em\u003eand \u003cem\u003eII\u003c/em\u003e managed to carve out a unique lane in a crowded field, and now both games have finally been updated with modern bells and whistles for current platforms.  - Ethan Gach \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/suikoden-1-2-hd-collection-review-rpg-features-ps1-1851767870\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/suikoden-1-2-hd-collection-review-rpg-features-ps1-1851767870\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967\" data-recommend-id=\"image://176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Mario, Luigi, and Yoshi stand in front of a Switch. \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Mario, Luigi, and Yoshi stand in front of a Switch. \" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"shutterstock\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Mario, Luigi, and Yoshi stand in front of a Switch. \" data-chomp-id=\"176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967\" data-format=\"png\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Mario, Luigi, and Yoshi stand in front of a Switch. \" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto: Michael San Diego (Shutterstock)\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967\" data-recommend-id=\"image://176d612b89f11d54b8eac6b9e64be967\" data-format=\"png\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Mario, Luigi, and Yoshi stand in front of a Switch. \" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe’re just a month out from the \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-release-date-april-2025-1851740848\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-release-date-april-2025-1851740848\"\u003ebig Nintendo Direct\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e giving us the full rundown on the Switch 2. Fans have been patiently waiting for the new hardware for years, excited to see what the future holds for the successor to one of the best video game consoles ever made. I’m excited too, but I also know that no matter what Nintendo has planed, the Switch 2 doesn’t have a prayer of recapturing the magic of the original Switch launch. Perhaps no future console does.  - Ethan Gach \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;